Debris on Highway 299 Leads to Two Vehicles in Collision - One Lane Closed for Clean Up
AI SUMMARY: A dispatch log from the California Highway Patrol reported a mud/dirt/rock slide at 4119 Highway 299 East in Trinity at mile marker 41.20. Two vehicles were involved, with one pulled to the shoulder and the other in the westbound lane with hazard lights on. The vehicle in the westbound lane was identified as a dark colored Chevrolet sedan. The information was relayed to the California Department of Transportation.
